---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import Sidebar from '../layouts/Sidebar.astro'
import Socials from '../content/socials.astro'
import MobileBottomNavbar from '../components/MobileBottomNavbar.astro'
---

<Base>
  <Sidebar style="terms">
    <section>
      <div class="content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: 16/04/2026</p>

        <p>
          Flüüfff ASBL is committed to protecting your personal data and respecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy
          explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Flüüfff ASBL</strong></li>
          <li>Gaversesteenweg 188</li>
          <li>9800 Deinze, Belgium</li>
          <li>Company number: 0662.498.716</li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://kbopub.economie.fgov.be/kbopub/toonondernemingps.html?ondernemingsnummer=662498716"
              target="_blank">Public registry entry</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>2. What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect and process the following personal data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Registration Information</strong>: Full name, date of birth, email address, postal address, phone
            number, and ID number (if required).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Event Participation</strong>: Nickname, country of origin, and optional profile picture (avatar) for
            badge printing and public attendee lists.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Communication</strong>: Email correspondence, including inquiries and support requests.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Payment Details</strong>: Transaction information (note: we do not store credit card numbers).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Website Usage</strong>: IP address, browser type, operating system, and pages visited (collected via
            cookies and analytics tools).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>Your personal data is used for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Event Management</strong>: Processing registrations, issuing badges, organizing accommodations, and
            managing event logistics.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Communication</strong>: Sending event-related information, updates, and responding to inquiries.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal Compliance</strong>: Fulfilling obligations under Belgian law, including accommodation records
            and tax regulations.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Website Improvement</strong>: Analyzing website usage to enhance user experience.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>4. Legal Base for Processing</h2>
        <p>We process your personal data based on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Contractual Necessity</strong>: To fulfill our obligations related to your event registration.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Legal Obligations</strong>: To comply with Belgian laws and regulations.</li>
          <li><strong>Consent</strong>: For optional services like newsletters and promotional materials.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legitimate Interests</strong>: To improve our services and ensure the security of our website.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>5. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
        <p>We may share your data with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Service Providers</strong>: Trusted partners who assist with event management, accommodation,
            payment processing, and IT services.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Legal Authorities</strong>: When required by law or to protect our legal rights.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          All third parties are contractually obligated to protect your data and use it solely for the purposes
          specified by Flüüfff ASBL.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Event Data</strong>: Up to one year after the event concludes.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Records</strong>: As required by Belgian law (e.g., financial records).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>After these periods, your data will be securely deleted or anonymized.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>7. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
        <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong>: Request a copy of your data.</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong>: Correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong>: Request deletion of your data.</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong>: Limit processing of your data.</li>
          <li><strong>Objection</strong>: Object to data processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
          <li><strong>Data Portability</strong>: Receive your data in a structured, commonly used format.</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw Consent</strong>: At any time, for processing based on consent.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us via the <a href="/contact">Contact</a> page.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>8. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data against unauthorized
          access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes encryption, access controls, and regular
          security assessments.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>9. Cookies and Website Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Our website uses cookies to enhance user experience and analyze site traffic. You can manage your cookie
          preferences through your browser settings. For more information, refer to our Cookie Policy.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated
          revision date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us via
          the <a href="/contact">Contact</a> page.
        </p>
      </div>
      <MobileBottomNavbar backHref="/conduct" backLabel="Code of Conduct" />
    </section>
  </Sidebar>

  <Socials />
</Base>
<style lang="scss">
  @use '../styles/text-styles';
  @use '../styles/charter';

  section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1200px;
    width: calc(100vw - 360px);
    margin: 0 auto;

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      width: 100vw;
    }
  }

  .content {
    padding: 20px 60px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: 100%;
    color: charter.$primary800;

    &:first-child {
      padding-top: 80px;
    }

    &:not(:has(~ .content)) {
      padding-bottom: 80px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      padding: 20px;

      &:first-child {
        padding-top: 40px;
      }

      &:not(:has(~ .content)) {
        padding-bottom: 40px;
      }
    }

    h1 {
      @include text-styles.heading1;
      margin-bottom: 16px;

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        @include text-styles.heading3;
      }
    }

    h2 {
      @include text-styles.heading4;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    p:not(:last-child),
    ul:not(:last-child) {
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    a {
      color: charter.$primary500;
    }

    ul > li {
      list-style-type: disc;
    }
  }
</style>
